b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Werdum vs. Volkov</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 127</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event produced by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> that was held on March 17, 2018, at <a href="/wiki/The_O2_Arena" title="The O2 Arena">The O<sub>2</sub> Arena</a> in <a href="/wiki/London" title="London">London</a>, <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">England</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A heavyweight bout between former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Heavyweight_Championship" title="UFC Heavyweight Championship">UFC Heavyweight Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Fabr%C3%ADcio_Werdum" title="Fabr\xc3\xadcio Werdum">Fabr\xc3\xadcio Werdum</a> and former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/List_of_Bellator_champions#Heavyweight_Championship" title="List of Bellator champions">Bellator Heavyweight Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Alexander_Volkov_(fighter)" title="Alexander Volkov (fighter)">Alexander Volkov</a> headlined this event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Promotional newcomer Dmitry Poberezhets was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Mark_Godbeer" title="Mark Godbeer">Mark Godbeer</a> at this event. However, Poberezhets was forced to pull out from the card on January 25 due to injury and was replaced by fellow newcomer Dmitry Sosnovskiy.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-anotherDmitry_4-0"><a href="#cite_note-anotherDmitry-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Rustam_Khabilov" title="Rustam Khabilov">Rustam Khabilov</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Kajan_Johnson" title="Kajan Johnson">Kajan Johnson</a> at this event. However, Khabilov pulled out of the fight on February 8 citing injury. Johnson is expected to remain on the card against <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Stevie_Ray_(MMA)" title="Stevie Ray (MMA)">Stevie Ray</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-JohnsonRay_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-JohnsonRay-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Elizeu_Zaleski_dos_Santos" title="Elizeu Zaleski dos Santos">Elizeu Zaleski dos Santos</a> was scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Jack_Marshman" title="Jack Marshman">Jack Marshman</a> at the event. However, Zaleski pulled out of the fight on February 19 citing a knee injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup> He was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Brad_Scott_(fighter)" title="Brad Scott (fighter)">Brad Scott</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup> In turn, Marshman was removed from the card two days before the event due to medical issues surrounding his weight cut and the bout was scrapped.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>On March 8, it was reported that Alex Reyes pulled out of his bout against <a href="/wiki/Nasrat_Haqparast" title="Nasrat Haqparast">Nasrat Haqparast</a> due to injury.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup> On March 12, <a href="/wiki/Nad_Narimani" title="Nad Narimani">Nad Narimani</a> was announced as his replacement.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup> The bout was scrapped minutes before the event as Haqparast was deemed unfit to fight by the medical team due to an <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Preseptal_cellulitis" title="Preseptal cellulitis">infectious eye condition</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-12"><a href="#cite_note-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-13"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>]'